<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1898-02-17T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1898-02-17T00:00:00-05:00" n="1089" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1089">
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Eguiguren</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Sherman</persName>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of Peru</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1898-02-17"><hi rend="italic">February 17,
                                    1898</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I perform the duty of expressing to the
                            United States Government the sentiments of condolence and sympathy of
                            the Government of Peru, together with my own, on account of the
                            catastrophe which has befallen the war steamer <hi rend="italic">Maine</hi> and the loss of the lives of so many citizens of the
                            United States.</p>
                        <p>Peru, which considers all the Republics of this continent as her sisters,
                            laments their misfortunes and feels them as she does her own. The grief,
                            therefore, which now afflicts the Great Republic is also ours.</p>
                        <p>I reiterate, etc.,</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Victor Eguiguren.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>